
[1]validity

   VALID'ITY, n.

   1. Strength or force to convince; justness; soundness; as the validity
   of an argument or proof; the validity of an objection.

   2. Legal strength or force; that quality of a thing which renders it
   supportable in law or equity; as the validity of a will; the validity
   of a grant; the validity of a claim or of a title. Certain forms and
   solemnities are usually requisite to give validity to contracts and
   conveyances of rights.

   3. Value. [Not in use.]
